Trebuie menÈionat cÄ estimatorul nedeplasat \(\hat{\sigma}^2\) pentru \(\sigma^2\) coincide, Ã®n cazul modelului (condiÈionat) normal (a se vedea secÈiunea Modelul (condiÈionat) normal), cu estimatorul de verosimilitate maximÄ restrÃ¢ns (REML - restricted maximum likelihood estimator) care este definit ca

\[ \underset{\sigma^2}{\arg\max}{\,L(\sigma^2;\boldsymbol Y)}, \]

unde \(L(\sigma^2;\boldsymbol Y)=\int L(\boldsymbol\beta, \sigma^2;\boldsymbol Y)\,d\boldsymbol\beta\). Ãn general acest estimator este mai puÈin deplasat faÈÄ de estimatorul de verosimilitate maximÄ Èi prin urmare este de preferat Ã®n practicÄ.

Folosind estimatorul \(\hat{\sigma}^2\) pentru \(\sigma^2\) putem construi un estimator \(\hat{\sigma}_{\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}}^2\) pentru varianÈa \(Var(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}) = \sigma^2 (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\):

\[ \hat{\sigma}_{\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}}^2 = \hat{\sigma}^2(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} = \frac{\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}\rVert^2}{n-(p+1)}(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}. \]

Ãn particular, un estimator pentru abaterea standard a estimatorului coeficientului \(\beta_j\), \(\hat{\beta}_j\), este dat de elementul \(j+1\) de pe diagonala matricii \((\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\):

\[ \hat{\sigma}_{\hat{\beta}_j} = \hat{\sigma}\sqrt{\left[(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\right]_{j+1,j+1}},\quad j = 0,1,\ldots,p. \]

Ãn exemplul urmÄtor vom ilustra numeric aceste rezultate:

Exemplu: preÈul chiriilor din Munchen

SÄ considerÄm modelul propus Ã®n Exemplul prin care exprimÄm preÈul mediu al chiriei pe metrul pÄtrat pentru locuinÈele din oraÈul Munchen Ã®n funcÈie de efectul invers proporÈional dat de suprafaÈa de locuit Èi de anul de construcÈie a apartamentului:

\[ pret{\_m^2}_i = \beta_0 + \beta_1\times \frac{1}{suprafata_i} + \beta_2\times an{\_con}_{i} + \varepsilon_i. \]

Matricea de design este

\[ \boldsymbol X = \begin{pmatrix}1 & \frac{1}{suprafata_1} & an{\_con}_1\\ 1 & \frac{1}{suprafata_2} & an{\_con}_2 \\ \vdots & \vdots & \vdots\\ 1 & \frac{1}{suprafata_{3082}} & an{\_con}_{3082}\end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix}1 & 0.029 & 1939\\1 & 0.01 & 1939\\ \vdots & \vdots & \vdots\\ 1 & 0.016 & 1953\end{pmatrix} \]

iar estimatorul coeficienÈilor de regresie obÈinut prin metoda celor mai mici pÄtrate este

\[ \hat{\boldsymbol \beta} = (\boldsymbol{X}^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol{X}^\intercal \boldsymbol Y = \begin{pmatrix}-65.406 \\ 119.361 \\ 0.036\end{pmatrix}. \] VarianÈa rezidualÄ estimatÄ \(\hat{\sigma}^2\) este \(\hat{\sigma}^2 = \frac{\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}\rVert^2}{n-(p+1)} = 4.3993026\) iar estimatorul matricei de varianÈÄ-covarianÈÄ \(Var(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}) = \sigma^2(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\) devine

\[ \hat{\sigma}_{\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}}^2 = \hat{\sigma}^2(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} = \begin{pmatrix}11.23 & 2.808 & -0.006\\ 2.808 & 31.767 & -0.002 \\ -0.006 & -0.002 & 0\end{pmatrix}. \]

Astfel gÄsim cÄ estimatorii pentru abaterile standard ale coeficienÈilor de regresie sunt \(\hat{\sigma}_{\hat{\beta}_0} = 3.3511\), \(\hat{\sigma}_{\hat{\beta}_1} = 5.6362\) Èi respectiv \(\hat{\sigma}_{\hat{\beta}_2} = 0.0017\). \(\square\)

4.4 PredicÈie

Unul dintre scopurile aplicÄrii unui model de regresie este acela de a prezice valoarea variabilei rÄspuns atunci cÃ¢nd avem de-a face cu un set nou de valori pentru variabilele explicative considerate Ã®n model. SÄ presupunem cÄ \((x_{n+1,1}, \ldots, x_{n+1,p})\) sunt valori ale variabilelor explicative ce corespund unei noi observaÈii Èi dorim sÄ prezicem \(y_{n+1}\) conform modelului de regresie liniarÄ

\[ y_{n+1} = \beta_0 + \beta_1 x_{n+1,1} + \cdots + \beta_p x_{n+1,p} + \varepsilon_{n+1} \]

pentru care \(\mathbb{E}[\varepsilon_{n+1}] = 0\), \(Var(\varepsilon_{n+1}) = \sigma^2\) Èi \(Cov(\varepsilon_{n+1}, \varepsilon_i)=0\) pentru \(i = 1,\ldots,n\). Metoda naturalÄ, este de a prezice valoarea corespunzÄtoare prin intermediul valorii ajustate \(\hat{y}_{n+1} = \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) unde \(\boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal = (1, x_{n+1,1}, \ldots, x_{n+1,p})\) Èi Ã®n acest caz eroarea de predicÈie este \(\hat{\varepsilon}_{n+1} = y_{n+1} - \hat{y}_{n+1}\).

Trebuie remarcat cÄ atunci cÃ¢nd vorbim de predicÈie putem sÄ ne referim sau la predicÈie asupra rÄspunsului mediu sau la predicÈie asupra unei noi valori. Ãn prima situaÈie ne referim la valoarea ajustatÄ \(x_{n+1}^\intercal\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) Ã®n care doar varianÈa lui \(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}\) este luatÄ Ã®n calcul atunci cÃ¢nd vorbim de variabilitatea predicÈiei. PlasÃ¢ndu-ne Ã®n contextul setului de date referitor la preÈul chiriilor din oraÈul Munchen, acest caz revine la a rÄspunde la Ã®ntrebare: Cu cÃ¢t se va Ã®nchiria, Ã®n medie, un apartament al cÄrui caracteristici sunt \((x_{n+1,1}, \ldots, x_{n+1,p})\) (suprafaÈÄ, an de construcÈie, etc.) ? A doua situaÈie se referÄ la preÈul de Ã®nchiriere \(x_{n+1}^\intercal\boldsymbol \beta + \varepsilon_{n+1}\) al unui nou apartament cu particularitÄÈile \((x_{n+1,1}, \ldots, x_{n+1,p})\). Ãn acest caz, variabilitatea predicÈiei vine din douÄ surse: varianÈa lui \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) Èi respectiv a termenului eroare \(\varepsilon_{n+1}\).

Rezultatul urmÄtor descrie varianÈa erorii de predicÈie.

Fie \((x_{n+1,1}, \ldots, x_{n+1,p})\) o nouÄ observaÈie Èi considerÄm \(\boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal = (1, x_{n+1,1}, \ldots, x_{n+1,p})\). Ne propunem sÄ prezicem valoarea \(y_{n+1}\) conform modelului

\[ y_{n+1} = \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal\boldsymbol \beta + \varepsilon_{n+1} \]

cu \(\mathbb{E}[\varepsilon_{n+1}] = 0\), \(Var(\varepsilon_{n+1}) = \sigma^2\) Èi \(Cov(\varepsilon_{n+1}, \varepsilon_i)=0\) pentru \(i = 1,\ldots,n\).

Atunci eroarea de predicÈie \(\hat{\varepsilon}_{n+1} = y_{n+1} - \hat{y}_{n+1}\) verificÄ proprietÄÈile

  1. \(\mathbb{E}[\hat{\varepsilon}_{n+1}] = 0\)

  2. \(Var(\hat{\varepsilon}_{n+1}) = \sigma^2\left(1 + \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol x_{n+1}\right)\)

  1. Cum \(\mathbb{E}[\varepsilon_{n+1}] = 0\) Èi ÈinÃ¢nd cont de nedeplasarea estimatorului \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) avem

\[ \mathbb{E}[\hat{\varepsilon}_{n+1}] = \mathbb{E}[ y_{n+1} - \hat{y}_{n+1}] = \mathbb{E}\left[\underbrace{\boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal \boldsymbol \beta + \varepsilon_{n+1}}_{y_{n+1}} - \underbrace{\boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}}_{\hat{y}_{n+1}}\right] \]

de unde \(\mathbb{E}[\hat{\varepsilon}_{n+1}] = \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal\left(\boldsymbol \beta - \mathbb{E}[\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}]\right) + \mathbb{E}[\varepsilon_{n+1}] = 0\).

Cum \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) depinde doar de variabilele \(\{\varepsilon_1,\ldots,\varepsilon_n\}\) iar \(Cov(\varepsilon_{n+1}, \varepsilon_i)=0\) pentru \(i = 1,\ldots,n\) deducem cÄ

\[\begin{align*} Var(\hat{\varepsilon}_{n+1}) &= Var\left(y_{n+1} - \hat{y}_{n+1}\right) = Var\left(\boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal\left(\boldsymbol \beta - \hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\right) + \varepsilon_{n+1}\right) \\ &= Var\left(\boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal\left(\boldsymbol \beta - \hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\right)\right) + Var(\varepsilon_{n+1}) = \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal Var(\boldsymbol \beta - \hat{\boldsymbol \beta}) \boldsymbol x_{n+1} + \sigma^2\\ &= \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal Var(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}) \boldsymbol x_{n+1} + \sigma^2 = \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal \sigma^2(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} \boldsymbol x_{n+1} + \sigma^2\\ &= \sigma^2\left(1 + \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol x_{n+1}\right). \square \end{align*}\]

ObservÄm astfel cÄ incertitudinea erorii de predicÈie este egalÄ cu suma incertitudinii datorate lui \(\boldsymbol \beta\), \(\sigma^2(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\), Èi cea datorate lui \(\varepsilon_{n+1}\), \(\sigma^2\).

Rezultatul urmÄtor generalizeazÄ rezultatul similar din cadrul modelului de regresie liniarÄ simplÄ.

Fie modelul de regresie \(\boldsymbol Y = \boldsymbol X\boldsymbol \beta + \boldsymbol \varepsilon\) unde matricea de design se scrie

\[ \boldsymbol {X}=\begin{pmatrix} 1 & x_{11} & \cdots & x_{1p}\\ \vdots & \vdots & \ddots & \vdots\\ 1 & x_{n1} & \cdots & x_{np} \end{pmatrix}_{n\times(p+1)} = \left[\underbrace{\boldsymbol X_0}_{\mathbf{1} = (1,\cdots,1)}|\boldsymbol X_1|\cdots|\boldsymbol X_p\right] = \left[\mathbf{1}|\boldsymbol Z\right] \]

cu \(\boldsymbol Z\) matricea de dimensiune \(n\times p\) formatÄ din coloanele \(\{\boldsymbol X_1,\ldots,\boldsymbol X_p\}\). Ãn contextul propoziÈiei precedente, fie \(\boldsymbol z_{n+1}^\intercal = (x_{n+1,1}, \ldots, x_{n+1,p})\) o nouÄ observaÈie Èi considerÄm \(\boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal = (1, \boldsymbol z_{n+1}^\intercal)\). ArÄtaÈi cÄ varianÈa erorii de predicÈie este

\[ Var(\hat{\varepsilon}_{n+1}) = \sigma^2\left[1 + \frac{1}{n} + \frac{1}{n}(\boldsymbol z_{n+1} - \bar{\boldsymbol x})^\intercal \boldsymbol \Gamma^{-1}(\boldsymbol z_{n+1} - \bar{\boldsymbol x})\right] \]

unde \(\boldsymbol \Gamma = \frac{1}{n}\boldsymbol Z^\intercal \boldsymbol Z - \bar{\boldsymbol x}\bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal\) este o matrice simetricÄ Èi pozitiv definitÄ atunci cÃ¢nd \(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X\) este inversabilÄ iar \(\bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal = (\bar{\boldsymbol x}_1, \ldots, \bar{\boldsymbol x}_p)\) cu \(\bar{\boldsymbol x}_j = \frac{1}{n}\sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_{ij}\).

Pentru Ã®nceput sÄ observÄm cÄ matricea \(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X\) se scrie sub forma

\[\begin{align*} \boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X &= \begin{bmatrix}\mathbf{1}^\intercal \\ \boldsymbol X_1^\intercal \\ \vdots \\ \boldsymbol X_p^\intercal\end{bmatrix}\begin{bmatrix}\mathbf{1} & \boldsymbol X_1 & \cdots &\boldsymbol X_p\end{bmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix}\underbrace{\mathbf{1}^\intercal\mathbf{1}}_{=n} & \underbrace{\mathbf{1}^\intercal\boldsymbol X_1}_{=n\bar{\boldsymbol x}_1} & \cdots & \underbrace{\mathbf{1}^\intercal\boldsymbol X_p}_{=n\bar{\boldsymbol x}_p}\\ \boldsymbol X_1^\intercal\mathbf{1} & \boldsymbol X_1^\intercal\boldsymbol X_1 & \cdots & \boldsymbol X_1^\intercal \boldsymbol X_p\\ \cdots & \cdots & \cdots & \cdots \\ \boldsymbol X_p^\intercal\mathbf{1} & \boldsymbol X_p^\intercal\boldsymbol X_1 & \cdots & \boldsymbol X_p^\intercal \boldsymbol X_p\end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix}n & n\bar{\boldsymbol x}_1 & \cdots & n\bar{\boldsymbol x}_p\\ n\bar{\boldsymbol x}_1 & \boldsymbol X_1^\intercal\boldsymbol X_1 & \cdots & \boldsymbol X_1^\intercal \boldsymbol X_p\\ \cdots & \cdots & \cdots & \cdots\\ n\bar{\boldsymbol x}_p & \boldsymbol X_p^\intercal\boldsymbol X_1 & \cdots & \boldsymbol X_p^\intercal \boldsymbol X_p\end{pmatrix}\\ &= \begin{pmatrix}n & n\bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal\\ n\bar{\boldsymbol x} & \boldsymbol Z^\intercal \boldsymbol Z\end{pmatrix} = n\begin{pmatrix}1 & \bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal\\ \bar{\boldsymbol x} & \frac{1}{n}\boldsymbol Z^\intercal \boldsymbol Z\end{pmatrix}. \end{align*}\]

Reamintim, e.g.Â (Henderson and Searle 1981) sau (Rencher and Schaalje 2008, Capitolul 2), cÄ dacÄ \(\boldsymbol F\) este o matrice pÄtratÄ inversabilÄ care se scrie sub formÄ de bloc de patru submatrice

\[ \boldsymbol F = \begin{pmatrix}\boldsymbol A & \boldsymbol B\\ \boldsymbol C & \boldsymbol D\end{pmatrix} \]

cu \(\boldsymbol A\) inversabilÄ atunci matricea \(\boldsymbol Q = \boldsymbol D - \boldsymbol C \boldsymbol A^{-1}\boldsymbol B\) este inversabilÄ iar inversa matricii \(\boldsymbol F\) este

\[ \boldsymbol F^{-1} = \begin{pmatrix}\boldsymbol A^{-1} + \boldsymbol A^{-1}\boldsymbol B \boldsymbol Q\boldsymbol C\boldsymbol A^{-1} & -\boldsymbol A^{-1}\boldsymbol B\boldsymbol Q\\ -\boldsymbol Q\boldsymbol C\boldsymbol A^{-1} & \boldsymbol Q\end{pmatrix}. \]

Ãn cazul problemei noastre avem \(\boldsymbol A = 1\), \(\boldsymbol B = \bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal\), \(\boldsymbol C = \bar{\boldsymbol x}\) Èi \(\boldsymbol D = \frac{1}{n}\boldsymbol Z^\intercal\boldsymbol Z\) prin urmare

\[ \boldsymbol Q = \boldsymbol D - \boldsymbol C \boldsymbol A^{-1}\boldsymbol B = \frac{1}{n}\boldsymbol Z^\intercal\boldsymbol Z - \bar{\boldsymbol x}\bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal = \boldsymbol \Gamma \]

iar

\[ \left(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X\right)^{-1} = \frac{1}{n}\begin{pmatrix}1 & \bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal\\ \bar{\boldsymbol x} & \frac{1}{n}\boldsymbol Z^\intercal \boldsymbol Z\end{pmatrix}^{-1} = \frac{1}{n}\begin{pmatrix}1 + \bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal\boldsymbol \Gamma^{-1}\bar{\boldsymbol x} & -\bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal\boldsymbol \Gamma^{-1}\\ -\boldsymbol \Gamma^{-1}\bar{\boldsymbol x} & \boldsymbol \Gamma^{-1}\end{pmatrix}. \] Dat fiind \(\boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal = (1, \boldsymbol z_{n+1}^\intercal)\) am vÄzut Ã®n PropoziÈia cÄ varianÈa erorii de predicÈie este datÄ de formula

\[ Var(\hat{\varepsilon}_{n+1}) = \sigma^2\left(1 + \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol x_{n+1}\right). \]

ÈinÃ¢nd cont de scrierea sub formÄ de blocuri a matricei \(\left(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X\right)^{-1}\) gÄsim cÄ

\[\begin{align*} \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol x_{n+1} &= \begin{pmatrix}1 & \boldsymbol z_{n+1}^\intercal\end{pmatrix} \frac{1}{n}\begin{pmatrix}1 + \bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal\boldsymbol \Gamma^{-1}\bar{\boldsymbol x} & -\bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal\boldsymbol \Gamma^{-1}\\ -\boldsymbol \Gamma^{-1}\bar{\boldsymbol x} & \boldsymbol \Gamma^{-1}\end{pmatrix} \begin{pmatrix}1\\ \boldsymbol z_{n+1}\end{pmatrix} \\ &= \frac{1}{n}\left(1 + \bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal\boldsymbol\Gamma^{-1}\bar{\boldsymbol x} - \boldsymbol z_{n+1}^\intercal \boldsymbol\Gamma^{-1}\bar{\boldsymbol x} - \bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal\boldsymbol\Gamma^{-1}\boldsymbol z_{n+1} + \boldsymbol z_{n+1}^\intercal\boldsymbol\Gamma^{-1}\boldsymbol z_{n+1}\right). \end{align*}\]

NotÃ¢nd cu \(\boldsymbol Z_c\) matricea (centratÄ) cu coloanele \(\boldsymbol X_j - \bar{\boldsymbol x}_j\mathbf{1}\), \(j = 1,\ldots,p\) putem observa cÄ

\[ \boldsymbol \Gamma = \frac{1}{n}\boldsymbol Z^\intercal\boldsymbol Z - \bar{\boldsymbol x}\bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal = \frac{1}{n}\boldsymbol Z_c^\intercal\boldsymbol Z_c \]

prin urmare \(\boldsymbol \Gamma = \boldsymbol \Gamma^\intercal\), deci \(\boldsymbol \Gamma\) este simetricÄ. Astfel, folosind faptul cÄ un scalar este egal cu transpusul sÄu, avem

\[ \boldsymbol z_{n+1}^\intercal \boldsymbol\Gamma^{-1}\bar{\boldsymbol x} = \left(\boldsymbol z_{n+1}^\intercal \boldsymbol\Gamma^{-1}\bar{\boldsymbol x}\right)^\intercal = \bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal\boldsymbol\Gamma^{-1}\boldsymbol z_{n+1} \]

ceea ce conduce la

\[\begin{align*} \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol x_{n+1} &= \frac{1}{n}\left(1 + \bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal\boldsymbol\Gamma^{-1}\bar{\boldsymbol x} - 2\bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal\boldsymbol\Gamma^{-1}\boldsymbol z_{n+1} + \boldsymbol z_{n+1}^\intercal\boldsymbol\Gamma^{-1}\boldsymbol z_{n+1}\right) \\ &= \frac{1}{n}\left[1 + (\boldsymbol z_{n+1} - \bar{\boldsymbol x})^\intercal \boldsymbol \Gamma^{-1}(\boldsymbol z_{n+1} - \bar{\boldsymbol x})\right] \end{align*}\]

de unde gÄsim

\[ Var(\hat{\varepsilon}_{n+1}) = \sigma^2\left[1 + \frac{1}{n} + \frac{1}{n}(\boldsymbol z_{n+1} - \bar{\boldsymbol x})^\intercal \boldsymbol \Gamma^{-1}(\boldsymbol z_{n+1} - \bar{\boldsymbol x})\right]. \]

Mai mult, sÄ remarcÄm cÄ dacÄ \(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X\) este inversabilÄ atunci matricea \(\boldsymbol \Gamma\) este pozitiv definitÄ. Ãntr-adevÄr am vÄzut cÄ \(\boldsymbol \Gamma = \frac{1}{n}\boldsymbol Z_c^\intercal\boldsymbol Z_c\) iar pentru \(\boldsymbol u \in\mathbb{R}^p\) putem scrie

\[ \boldsymbol u^\intercal \boldsymbol \Gamma\boldsymbol u = \frac{1}{n}\boldsymbol u^\intercal \boldsymbol Z_c^\intercal\boldsymbol Z_c \boldsymbol u = \frac{1}{n}\lVert\boldsymbol Z_c \boldsymbol u\rVert^2 \geq 0 \]

deci \(\boldsymbol \Gamma\) este pozitiv semidefinitÄ. Avem egalitate \(\frac{1}{n}\lVert\boldsymbol Z_c \boldsymbol u\rVert^2 = 0\) atunci cÃ¢nd \(\boldsymbol Z_c \boldsymbol u = 0\) sau, altfel spus, atunci cÃ¢nd

\[ u_1(\boldsymbol X_1 - \bar{\boldsymbol x}_1\mathbf{1}) + \cdots + u_p(\boldsymbol X_p - \bar{\boldsymbol x}_p\mathbf{1}) = 0 \iff \sum_{j=1}^{n}u_j\boldsymbol X_j = \left(\sum_{j=1}^{n}u_j\bar{\boldsymbol x}_j\right)\mathbf{1}. \]

AceastÄ ultimÄ relaÈie ne spune cÄ prima coloanÄ a lui \(\boldsymbol X\) se scrie ca o combinaÈie liniarÄ de celelalte, ceea ce Ã®nseamnÄ cÄ \(\mathrm{rang}(\boldsymbol X)\leq p\) de unde concluzionÄm cÄ matricea \(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X\) nu este inversabilÄ. \(\square\)

Este interesant de remarcat cum din faptul cÄ \(\boldsymbol \Gamma\) este simetricÄ Èi pozitiv definitÄ deducem cÄ \((\boldsymbol z_{n+1} - \bar{\boldsymbol x})^\intercal \boldsymbol \Gamma^{-1}(\boldsymbol z_{n+1} - \bar{\boldsymbol x})\geq 0\), cu egalitate dacÄ Èi numai dacÄ \(\boldsymbol z_{n+1} = \bar{\boldsymbol x}\), adicÄ \(\boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal = (1, \boldsymbol z_{n+1}^\intercal) = (1, \bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal)\). Ãn acest caz \(Var(\hat{\varepsilon}_{n+1}) = \sigma^2\left(1+\frac{1}{n}\right)\), rezultat care generalizeazÄ rezultatul corespunzÄtor de la regresia liniarÄ simplÄ: trebuie sÄ ne plasÄm Ã®n centrul norului de puncte ale variabilelor explicative pentru a prezice variabila rÄspuns cu mai multÄ precizie.

5 InterpretÄri geometrice - coeficientul de determinare

Ãn aceastÄ secÈiune vom prezenta descompunerea ANOVA a modelului de regresie, vom defini, dintr-o perspectivÄ geometricÄ, coeficientul de determinare multiplÄ Èi vom investiga o serie de proprietÄÈi ale acestuia.

Vom considera atÃ¢t modelul de regresie liniarÄ multiplÄ Ã®n care este inclus termenul liber cÃ¢t Èi cel Ã®n care acesta nu apare. Fie astfel, modelul de regresie liniarÄ \(\boldsymbol Y = \boldsymbol X\boldsymbol \beta + \boldsymbol \varepsilon\) Ã®n care \(\boldsymbol Y\in\mathbb{R}^n\) este vectorul rÄspuns, \(\boldsymbol X = \left[\mathbf{1}|\boldsymbol X_1|\cdots|\boldsymbol X_p\right]\in\mathcal{M}_{n, p+1}(\mathbb{R})\) sau \(\boldsymbol X = \left[\boldsymbol X_1|\cdots|\boldsymbol X_p\right]\in\mathcal{M}_{n, p}(\mathbb{R})\) (pentru modelul fÄrÄ termenul liber) este matricea de design (\(\mathrm{rang}(\boldsymbol X) = p+1\) respectiv \(\mathrm{rang}(\boldsymbol X) = p\)), \(\boldsymbol \beta\in\mathbb{R}^{p+1}\) sau \(\boldsymbol \beta\in\mathbb{R}^{p}\) este vectorul parametrilor dupÄ caz Èi \(\boldsymbol \varepsilon\in\mathbb{R}^n\) este vectorul termenilor eroare.

NotÄm, ca Èi pÃ¢nÄ acum, cu \(\mathcal{M}(X)\) subspaÈiul generat de coloanele matricii \(\boldsymbol X\), cu \(\mathcal{M}(X)^\perp\) subspaÈiul ortogonal, cu \(\hat{\boldsymbol Y} = \boldsymbol X\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}\) proiecÈia ortogonalÄ a lui \(\boldsymbol Y\) pe \(\mathcal{M}(X)\) Èi cu \(\hat{\boldsymbol\varepsilon} = \boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}\in\mathcal{M}(X)^\perp\) vectorul valorilor reziduale.

DacÄ modelul de regresie considerat nu include termenul liber (\(\beta_0\)) atunci, conform figurii de mai sus, observÄm cÄ putem aplica Teorema lui Pitagora direct (Ã®n triunghiul determinat de \(\boldsymbol Y\), \(\hat{\boldsymbol Y}\) Èi \(\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}\)) Èi obÈinem cÄ

\[ \begin{aligned} \lVert \boldsymbol Y\rVert^2 &= \lVert \hat{\boldsymbol Y}\rVert^2 + \lVert\hat{\boldsymbol\varepsilon}\rVert^2\\ &= \lVert \boldsymbol X \hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\rVert^2 + \lVert \boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol X \hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\rVert^2\\ SS_T &= SS_{reg} + RSS. \end{aligned} \]

Pe de altÄ parte, atunci cÃ¢nd modelul include Èi termenul liber (cum este cazul Ã®n cele mai multe aplicaÈii), atunci tot prin aplicarea Teoremei lui Pitagora, dar de aceastÄ datÄ Ã®n triunghiul albastru, are loc urmÄtoarea descompunere (descompunerea ANOVA pentru regresie)

\[ \begin{aligned} \lVert \boldsymbol Y - \bar{\boldsymbol y}\mathbf{1}\rVert^2 &= \lVert \hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \bar{\boldsymbol y}\mathbf{1}\rVert^2 + \lVert\hat{\boldsymbol\varepsilon}\rVert^2\\ SS_T &= SS_{reg} + RSS\\ \end{aligned} \]

unde

  • \(SS_{T} = \lVert \boldsymbol Y - \bar{\boldsymbol y}\mathbf{1}\rVert^2\) se numeÈte suma abaterilor pÄtratice totale (variaÈia totalÄ)

  • \(SS_{reg} = \lVert \hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \bar{\boldsymbol y}\mathbf{1}\rVert^2\) se numeÈte suma abaterilor pÄtratice de regresie (variaÈia explicatÄ de model)

  • \(RSS = \lVert \boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}\rVert^2 = \lVert\hat{\boldsymbol\varepsilon}\rVert^2\) se numeÈte suma abaterilor pÄtratice reziduale (variaÈia rezidualÄ)

astfel

\[ \text{VariaÈia totalÄ} = \text{VariaÈia explicatÄ de regresie } + \text{ VariaÈia rezidualÄ}. \]

Coeficientul de determinare \(R^2\) (Ã®n R are denumirea de \(\texttt{Multiple R-Squared}\)) este definit prin

\[ R^2 = \cos^2(\theta_0) = \frac{\lVert \hat{\boldsymbol Y}\rVert^2}{\lVert \boldsymbol Y\rVert^2} = 1 - \frac{\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol\varepsilon}\rVert^2}{\lVert \boldsymbol Y\rVert^2} = 1 - \frac{RSS}{SS_T} \]

atunci cÃ¢nd termenul liber nu este inclus Ã®n model Èi prin

\[ R^2 = \cos^2(\theta) = \frac{\text{VariaÈia explicatÄ de model}}{\text{VariaÈia totalÄ}} = \frac{\lVert \hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \bar{\boldsymbol y}\mathbf{1}\rVert^2}{\lVert \boldsymbol Y - \bar{\boldsymbol y}\mathbf{1}\rVert^2} = 1 - \frac{\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol\varepsilon}\rVert^2}{\lVert \boldsymbol Y - \bar{\boldsymbol y}\mathbf{1}\rVert^2} = 1 - \frac{RSS}{SS_T} \]

atunci cÃ¢nd termenul liber este inclus Ã®n model.

Din descompunerea ANOVA pentru regresie putem interpreta coeficientul de determinare (procentul din varianÈa totalÄ explicat de model) astfel: cu cÃ¢t este mai aproape \(R^2\) de \(1\) cu atÃ¢t este mai micÄ suma abaterilor pÄtratice reziduale \(\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol\varepsilon}\rVert^2 = \sum_{i=1}^{n}\hat{\varepsilon}_i^2\), prin urmare cu atÃ¢t este mai bunÄ potrivirea modelului pe date (fitul) - cazul extrem Ã®n care avem \(R^2 = 1\) implicÄ \(\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol\varepsilon}\rVert^2 = 0\) ceea ce Ã®nseamnÄ cÄ punctele se regÄsesc Ã®n hiperplanul de regresie Èi avem potrivire perfectÄ; pe de altÄ parte, cu cÃ¢t \(R^2\) este mai aproape de \(0\), cu atÃ¢t potrivirea pe date este slabÄ (fitul nu este prea bun) - cazul limitÄ \(R^2 = 0\) implicÄ faptul cÄ predicÈia rÄspunsului \(y_i\) este Ã®ntotdeauna egalÄ cu media \(\bar{y}\) rÄspunsului Èi nu depinde de valorile covariabilelor, ceea ce atatÄ cÄ acestea nu au niciun impact asupra explicÄrii modelului.

Trebuie sÄ Èinem cont cÄ suntem Ã®n ipoteza Ã®n care modelul liniar considerat este adecvat datelor, Ã®n caz contrar (i.e.Â atunci cÃ¢nd existÄ relaÈii neliniare Ã®ntre covariabile Èi rÄspuns), Ã®n care modelul nu este specificat corespunzÄtor, putem avea un coeficient de determinare apropiat de \(0\) Èi cu toate acestea covariabilele sÄ aibÄ o mare putere explicativÄ asupra rÄspunsului. Prin urmare, folosirea coeficientului de determinare ca (singurÄ) mÄsurÄ de ajustare a modelului se poate dovedi Ã®nÈelÄtoare.

Ãn figura urmÄtoare avem diagramele de Ã®mprÄÈtiere a patru modele simulate care Ã®ntorc aproximativ acelaÈi coeficient de determinare \(R^2 \approx 0.76\). DacÄ Ã®n figura din stÃ¢nga sus avem un exemplu de situaÈie normalÄ, Ã®n figura din dreapta sus variaÈia rezidualÄ este mai scÄzutÄ decÃ¢t cea din primul grafic dar atunci Èi variaÈia lui \(x\) este mai micÄ conducÃ¢nd la o valoare similarÄ a lui \(R^2\). Figura din stÃ¢nga jos aratÄ o corelaÈie puternicÄ Ã®ntre rÄspuns Èi variabila explicativÄ (un coeficient de corelaÈie de \(0.954\)), cu excepÈia a douÄ observaÈii aberante (outlier) iar figura din dreapta jos prezintÄ un model specificat incorect, relaÈia fiind una pÄtraticÄ.

Este important de remarcat Èi cÄ Ã®n modelul de regresie liniarÄ multiplÄ, ca Èi Ã®n cazul modelului de regresie liniarÄ simplÄ, putem interpreta coeficientul de determinare ca fiind pÄtratul coeficientului de corelaÈie dintre rÄspuns \(y_i\) Èi valorile ajustate \(\hat{y}_i\): \(R^2 = r_{\boldsymbol Y\hat{\boldsymbol Y}}^2\).

Atunci cÃ¢nd vrem sÄ comparÄm diferite modele pe baza coeficientului de determinare, trebuie sÄ avem grijÄ ca urmÄtoarele condiÈii sÄ fie Ã®ndeplinite:

  • fiecare model trebuie sÄ aibÄ aceeaÈi variabilÄ rÄspuns, nu putem compara modele Ã®n care primul area ca variabilÄ rÄspuns pe \(y\) iar al doilea pe \(h(y)\), \(h\) o transformare

  • fiecare model trebuie sÄ aibÄ acelaÈi numÄr de parametrii

  • fiecare model trebuie sÄ includÄ termenul liber

Astfel, Ã®n general, nu putem folosi coeficientul de determinare pentru compararea modelelor dupÄ cum se vede Èi Ã®n exemplul urmÄtor.

Exemplu: preÈul chiriilor din Munchen - compararea modelelor dupÄ \(R^2\)

DupÄ cum am vÄzut Ã®n exemplele Èi , putem explicita relaÈia dintre preÈul chiriei pe metrul pÄtrat al aparamentelor din Munchen Ã®n funcÈie de suprafaÈa de locuit a acestora prin diferite modele de regresie liniarÄ:

\[ \begin{aligned} M_1 &: pret{\_m^2}_i = \beta_0 + \beta_1 \times suprafata_i + \varepsilon_i,\\ M_2 &: pret{\_m^2}_i = \beta_0 + \beta_1 \times \frac{1}{suprafata_i} + \varepsilon_i, \\ M_3 &: pret{\_m^2}_i = \beta_0 + \beta_1 \times suprafata_i + \beta_2 \times suprafata_i^2 + \varepsilon_i\\ M_4 &: pret{\_m^2}_i = \beta_0 + \beta_1 \times suprafata_i + \beta_2 \times suprafata_i^2 + \beta_3 \times suprafata_i^3 + \varepsilon_i \end{aligned} \] Tabelul de mai jos include modelele estimate Ã®mpreunÄ cu coeficienÈii de determinare corespunzÄtori:

Modelul Modelul estimat Coeficientul de determinare \(R^2\)
\(M_1\) \(\widehat{pret{\_m^2}_i} = 9.469 140.178 \times suprafata_i\) 0.116
\(M_2\) \(\widehat{pret{\_m^2}_i} = 4.732 + 140.178\times \frac{1}{suprafata_i}\) 0.154
\(M_3\) \(\widehat{pret{\_m^2}_i} = 11.83 -0.106\times suprafata_i + 4.7\times 10^{-4}\times suprafata_i^2\) 0.143
\(M_4\) \(\widehat{pret{\_m^2}_i} = 14.28 -0.218\times suprafata_i + 0.002\times suprafata_i^2 -6\times 10^{-6}\times suprafata_i^3\) 0.15

Se observÄ cÄ pentru toate cele patru modele, coeficientul de determinare este relativ scÄzut motivul principal fiind cÄ, pe lÃ¢ngÄ variabilitatea mare a datelor, modelele nu includ o mare parte din covariabilele cu mare impact explicativ.

DacÄ ne uitÄm la primele douÄ modele, observÄm cÄ \(M_2\) are un coeficient de determinare mai mare \(R^2_{M_2} = 0.154 \geq R^2_{M_2} = 0.116\). Cum ambele modele conÈin acelaÈi numÄr de parametrii deducem cÄ acest model este de preferat Ã®ntre cele douÄ. DacÄ ne uitÄm la modelele \(M_1\), \(M_3\) Èi \(M_4\) constatÄm cÄ acestea sunt modele imbricate (nested models) ceea ce Ã®nseamnÄ cÄ modelul \(M_4\) include atÃ¢t modelul \(M_3\) (\(\beta_3 = 0\)) cÃ¢t Èi pe \(M_1\) (\(\beta_3 = \beta_2 = 0\)) iar modelul \(M_3\) Ã®l conÈine pe \(M_1\) ca Èi caz particular (\(\beta_2 = 0\)). DupÄ cum vom vedea Ã®n PropoziÈia , asta implicÄ faptul cÄ \(M_1\) are cel mai mic coeficient de determinare Ã®ntre cele trei modele, \(M_3\) are al doilea cel mai mic \(R^2\) iar \(M_4\) are cel mai mare \(R^2\). O comparaÈie Ã®ntre cele trei modele, Ã®n funcÈie de \(R^2\), Ã®n acest caz nu este recomandatÄ deoarece modelele au un numÄr diferit de parametrii. Este de asemenea important de remarcat faptul cÄ un model cu un numÄr mai mare de parametrii nu implicÄ neapÄrat cÄ are Èi un coeficient de determinare mai mare faÈÄ de un model cu un numÄr mai mic de parametrii. Acest fenomen se observÄ atunci cÃ¢nd comparÄm \(M_2\) cu \(M_3\), \(R^2_{M_2} = 0.154 \geq R^2_{M_3} = 0.143\). Ãn acest caz, modelul \(M_2\) este de preferat modelului \(M_3\) deoarece conÈine un numÄr mai mic de parametrii Èi are un coeficient \(R^2\) mai mare. \(\square\)

Cum coeficientul de determinare \(R^2 = 1 - \frac{RSS}{SS_{T}} = 1 - \frac{\hat{\sigma}}{SS_{T}}[n-(p+1)]\) observÄm cÄ acesta creÈte odatÄ cu numÄrul de variabile explicative \(p\). Ãn cele ce urmeazÄ vom defini o variantÄ a coeficientului de determinare care sÄ amelioreze aceastÄ problemÄ. Cum \(R^2\) nu Èine cont de dimensiunea spaÈiului \(\mathcal{M}(X)\) se defineÈte coeficientul de determinare ajustat \(R_a^2\) (Ã®n R are denumirea de \(\texttt{Adjusted R-Squared}\)) prin

Coeficientul de determinare ajustat \(R_a^2\) este definit prin

\[ R_a^2 = 1 - \frac{\frac{\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol\varepsilon}\rVert^2}{n-(p+1)}}{\frac{\lVert \boldsymbol Y \rVert^2}{n}} = 1 - \frac{n}{n-(p+1)}\frac{\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol\varepsilon}\rVert^2}{\lVert \boldsymbol Y \rVert^2} = 1 - \frac{n}{n-(p+1)}(1 - R^2) \]

atunci cÃ¢nd termenul liber nu este inclus Ã®n model Èi respectiv prin

\[ R_a^2 = 1 - \frac{\frac{\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol\varepsilon}\rVert^2}{n-(p+1)}}{\frac{\lVert \boldsymbol Y - \bar{\boldsymbol y}\mathbf{1}\rVert^2}{n-1}} = 1 - \frac{n-1}{n-(p+1)}\frac{\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol\varepsilon}\rVert^2}{\lVert \boldsymbol Y - \bar{\boldsymbol y}\mathbf{1}\rVert^2} = 1 - \frac{n-1}{n-(p+1)}(1 - R^2). \]

atunci cÃ¢nd termenul liber este inclus Ã®n model.

Ajustarea corespunde la Ã®mpÄrÈirea normelor la pÄtrat cu dimensiunea subspaÈiului din care fac parte vectorii. NotÄm de asemenea cÄ \(R^2_a\) nu mai mÄsoarÄ proporÈia variabilitÄÈii lui \(y\) explicate de modelul de regresie Èi Ã®n plus \(R^2_a\leq 1\) Èi poate lua chiar Èi valori negative.

Exemplu: compararea coeficienÈilor de determinare \(R^2\) Èi \(R^2_{a}\)

Pentru a vedea diferenÈa dintre cei doi coeficienÈi de determinare considerÄm urmÄtorul studiu de simulare Ã®n care presupunem cÄ generÄm observaÈiile \(x_{i1}, x_{i2}, x_{i3}, y_i\) pentru \(i = 1,2,\ldots,n =100\) conform modelului de regresie liniarÄ

\[ y_i = \beta_0 + \beta_1 x_{i1} + \beta_2 x_{i2} + \beta_3 x_{i3} + \varepsilon_i, \]

unde \(x_1,x_2, x_3\sim \mathcal{N}(0,1)\) Èi \(\varepsilon_i\sim \mathcal{N}(0, 9)\). La aceste date adÄugÄm \(p-3 = 94\) variabile explicative fictive \(x_j\sim\mathcal{N}(0,1)\) care sunt independente de \(y\) rezultÃ¢nd Ã®ntr-un total de \(p=97\) covariabile dintre care doar primele douÄ (\(x_1\) Èi \(x_2\)) sunt relevante Ã®n explicarea rÄspunsului. CalculÄm coeficienÈii de determinare \(R^2(j)\) Èi respectiv \(R^2_a(j)\) pentru fiecare dintre modelele

\[ y = \beta_0 + \beta_1 x_{1} + \beta_2 x_{2} + \cdots + \beta_j x_{j} + \varepsilon, \]

unde \(j = 1, 2, \ldots, p\) Èi trasÄm pe acelaÈi grafic curbele \((j, R^2(j))\) Èi \((j, R^2_a(j))\). Cum \(R^2\) Èi \(R^2_a\) sunt variabile aleatoare, repetÄm experimentul de \(M = 200\) ori. Rezultatele sunt ilustrate Ã®n figura de mai jos (curbele Ã®ngroÈate sunt curbele medii). Putem observa cÄ \(R^2\) creÈte liniar odatÄ cu numÄrul de predictori din model chiar dacÄ doar primii trei predictori sunt relevanÈi Ã®n explicarea lui \(y\). Pe de altÄ parte \(R^2_a\) creÈte Ã®n primele trei covariabile dupÄ care descreÈte Ã®ncet arÄtÃ¢nd cÄ, Ã®n medie, numÄrul optim de covariabile din model sunt Ã®n jurul lui \(p = 3\). Cu toate acestea se constatÄ cÄ \(R^2_a\) are o variabilitate mare atunci cÃ¢nd \(p\) se apropie de \(n-3\), o consecinÈÄ a factorului \(n-1\). \(\square\)

UrmÄtorul exerciÈiu este o aplicaÈie numericÄ de calcul a coeficienÈilor de determinare Ã®n contextul unui model de regresie cu douÄ covariabile.

Ne propunem sÄ determinÄm evoluÈia unei variabile rÄspuns \(y_i\) Ã®n funcÈie de douÄ variabile explicative \(x_i\) Èi \(z_i\). Fie \(\boldsymbol X = (\mathbf{1}, \boldsymbol x, \boldsymbol z)\) matricea de design.

  1. Am obÈinut rezultatele urmÄtoare

\[ \boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X = \begin{pmatrix}25 & 0 & 0\\ ? & 9.3 & 5.4\\ ? & ? & 12.7\end{pmatrix} \]

  1. DeterminaÈi valorile care lipsesc (?).
  2. CÃ¢t este \(n\) ?
  3. CalculaÈi coeficientul de corelaÈie dintre \(\boldsymbol x\) Èi \(\boldsymbol z\).
  1. Modelul de regresie liniarÄ a lui \(\boldsymbol Y\) Ã®n funcÈie de \(\mathbf{1}, \boldsymbol x, \boldsymbol z\) este

\[ \boldsymbol Y = -1.6\boldsymbol 1 + 0.61 \boldsymbol x + 0.46 \boldsymbol z + \hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}, \quad \lVert\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}\rVert^2 = 0.3 \]

  1. DeterminaÈi \(\bar{\boldsymbol y}\).
  2. CalculaÈi suma abaterilor pÄtratice de regresie \(SS_{reg}\), suma abaterilor pÄtratice totale \(SS_T\), coeficientul de determinare Èi coeficientul de determinare ajustat.
    1. Pentru a determina cele trei valori care lipsesc sÄ notÄm cÄ matricea \(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X\) este simetricÄ, prin urmare \(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X = \left(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X\right)^\intercal\) de unde

\[ \begin{pmatrix}25 & 0 & 0\\ ? & 9.3 & 5.4\\ ? & ? & 12.7\end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix}25 & ? & ?\\ 0 & 9.3 & ?\\ 0 & 5.4 & 12.7\end{pmatrix} \]

ceea ce conduce la valorile \(0, 0, 5.4\).

  1. Pentru a determina valoarea lui \(n\) sÄ observÄm cÄ

\[ \boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X = \begin{pmatrix}\mathbf{1}^\intercal \\ \boldsymbol x^\intercal\\ \boldsymbol z^\intercal\end{pmatrix}\begin{pmatrix}\mathbf{1} & \boldsymbol x & \boldsymbol z\end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix}\mathbf{1}^\intercal \mathbf{1} & \mathbf{1}^\intercal\boldsymbol x & \mathbf{1}^\intercal\boldsymbol z \\ \boldsymbol x^\intercal\mathbf{1} & \boldsymbol x^\intercal\boldsymbol x & \boldsymbol x^\intercal\boldsymbol z\\ \boldsymbol z^\intercal\mathbf{1} & \boldsymbol z^\intercal\boldsymbol x & \boldsymbol z^\intercal\boldsymbol z\end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix}n & n\bar x & n\bar z \\ n\bar x & \boldsymbol x^\intercal\boldsymbol x & \boldsymbol x^\intercal\boldsymbol z\\ n\bar z & \boldsymbol z^\intercal\boldsymbol x & \boldsymbol z^\intercal\boldsymbol z\end{pmatrix} \]

ceea ce aratÄ cÄ \(n = \left(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X\right)_{1,1} = 25\).

  1. Coeficientul de corelaÈie dintre \(\boldsymbol x\) Èi \(\boldsymbol z\) este dat de

\[ r_{\boldsymbol x,\boldsymbol z} = \frac{\sum_{i=1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)(z_i - \bar z)}{\sqrt{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}\sqrt{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(z_i - \bar z)^2}} \]

Èi cum, din punctul anterior, \(\bar x = \frac{\left(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X\right)_{1,2}}{n} = 0\) Èi \(\bar z = \frac{\left(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X\right)_{1,3}}{n} = 0\) deci

\[ r_{\boldsymbol x,\boldsymbol z} = \frac{\sum_{i=1}^{n}x_iz_i}{\sqrt{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_i^2}\sqrt{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}z_i^2}} = \frac{\boldsymbol x^\intercal\boldsymbol z}{\sqrt{\boldsymbol x^\intercal\boldsymbol x}\sqrt{\boldsymbol z^\intercal\boldsymbol z}} = \frac{\left(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X\right)_{2,3}}{\sqrt{\left(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X\right)_{2,2}}\sqrt{\left(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X\right)_{3,3}}} = \frac{5.4}{\sqrt{9.3}\sqrt{12.7}}\approx 0.5 \]

    1. Avem modelul

\[ y_i = -1.6 + 0.61 x_i + 0.46 z_i + \hat{\varepsilon}_i \]

care prin sumare devine

\[ \bar y = -1.6 + 0.61 \bar x + 0.46 \bar z + \frac{1}{n}\sum_{i=1}^{n}\hat{\varepsilon}_i. \]

Cum \(\mathbf{1}\) aparÈine modelului, deci \(\mathbf{1}\in\mathcal{M}(\boldsymbol X)\) Èi ÈinÃ¢nd cont de faptul cÄ \(\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}\in\mathcal{M}(X)^\perp\) deducem cÄ \(\langle\mathbf{1}, \hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}\rangle = 0\) sau \(\frac{1}{n}\sum_{i=1}^{n}\hat{\varepsilon}_i = 0\). Astfel

\[ \bar y = -1.6 + 0.61 \underbrace{\bar x}_{=0} + 0.46 \underbrace{\bar z}_{= 0} + \underbrace{\frac{1}{n}\sum_{i=1}^{n}\hat{\varepsilon}_i}_{=0} = -1.6. \]

  1. Avem cÄ suma abaterilor pÄtratice explicate de model este datÄ de

\[ SS_{reg} = \lVert\hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \bar y\mathbf{1}\rVert^2 = \sum_{i=1}^{n}(\hat{y}_i - \bar y)^2 = \sum_{i=1}^{n}(0.61 x_i + 0.46 z_i)^2 \]

adicÄ

\[\begin{align*} SS_{reg} &= \lVert\hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \bar y\mathbf{1}\rVert^2 = 0.61^2\sum_{i=1}^{n}x_i^2 + 2\times 0.61\times 0.46\sum_{i=1}^{n}x_iz_i + 0.46^2\sum_{i=1}^{n}z_i^2\\ &= 0.61^2\left(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X\right)_{2,2} + 2\times 0.61\times 0.46\left(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X\right)_{2,3} + 0.46^2\left(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X\right)_{3,3} = 9.18. \end{align*}\]

Suma abaterilor pÄtratice totale se determinÄ folosind formula de descompunere a varianÈei:

\[ \underbrace{SS_T}_{\lVert\boldsymbol Y - \bar y\mathbf{1}\rVert^2} = \underbrace{SS_{reg}}_{\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \bar y\mathbf{1}\rVert^2} + \underbrace{RSS}_{\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}\rVert^2} = 9.18 + 0.3 = 9.48. \]

Coeficientul de determinare \(R^2\) este

\[ R^2 = \frac{SS_{reg}}{SS_T} = \frac{9.18}{9.48}\approx 0.968 \]

ceea ce aratÄ cÄ aproximativ \(97\%\) din variabilitatea datelor este explicatÄ de modelul de regresie iar coeficientul de determinare ajustat este

\[ R_1^2 = 1 - \frac{n-1}{n-(p+1)}\frac{\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol\varepsilon}\rVert^2}{\lVert \boldsymbol Y - \bar{\boldsymbol y}\mathbf{1}\rVert^2} = 1 - \frac{n-1}{n-(p+1)}\left(1 - R^2\right) = 1 - \frac{25 - 1}{25 - (2 + 1)}(1-0.968)\approx 0.965 \]

ceea ce verificÄ relaÈia generalÄ \(R_a^2<R^2\). \(\square\)

UrmÄtorul rezultat justificÄ relaÈia care existÄ Ã®ntre coeficienÈii de determinare Ã®n cazul modelelor imbricate.

Fie \(\boldsymbol Z\in\mathcal{M}_{n,q}(\mathbb{R})\) o matrice de rang \(q\) Èi \(\boldsymbol X\in\mathcal{M}_{n,p}(\mathbb{R})\) o matrice de rang \(p\), \(p>q\), compusÄ din cei \(q\) vectori coloanÄ ai lui \(\boldsymbol Z\) Èi din alÈi \(p-q\) vectori liniar independenÈi. ConsiderÄm modelele urmÄtoare:

\[\begin{align*} \boldsymbol Y &= \boldsymbol Z\boldsymbol \beta + \boldsymbol\varepsilon,\\ \boldsymbol Y &= \boldsymbol X\boldsymbol \gamma + \boldsymbol\eta \end{align*}\]

Presupunem, pentru simplitate, cÄ niciun model nu conÈine termenul liber (constanta). NotÄm cu \(P_X\) Èi \(P_Z\) matricele de proiecÈie ortogonalÄ pe subspaÈiile \(\mathcal{M}(X)\) Èi respectiv \(\mathcal{M}(Z)\), generate de coloanele lui \(\boldsymbol X\) Èi \(\boldsymbol Z\). De asemenea notÄm cu \(P_{X\cap Z^\perp}\) matricea de proiecÈie ortogonalÄ pe \(\mathcal{M}(X)\cap \mathcal{M}(Z)^\perp\), subspaÈiul ortogonal al lui \(\mathcal{M}(Z)\) din \(\mathcal{M}(X)\), astfel

\[ \mathbb{R}^n = \mathcal{M}(X) \oplus \mathcal{M}(X)^\perp = \left(\mathcal{M}(Z) \oplus \left(\mathcal{M}(X)\cap \mathcal{M}(Z)^\perp\right) \right) \oplus \mathcal{M}(X)^\perp \]

Atunci:

  1. Are loc relaÈia \(\lVert P_X\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2 = \lVert P_Z\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2 + \lVert P_{X\cap Z^\perp}\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2\).

  2. Ãntre coeficienÈii de determinare ai celor douÄ modele existÄ inegalitatea \(R_X^2\geq R_Z^2\).

AceastÄ propoziÈie face referire la modele imbricate - nested models.

  1. Deoarece \(\mathcal{M}(\boldsymbol Z)\subset\mathcal{M}(\boldsymbol X)\) Èi aplicÃ¢nd teorema celor trei perpendiculare3 avem, vezi figura de mai jos,

\[\begin{align*} \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_p &= P_X\boldsymbol Y = (\underbrace{P_Z + P_{Z^\perp}}_{I}) P_X\boldsymbol Y = P_Z P_X \boldsymbol Y + P_{Z^\perp}P_X\boldsymbol Y\\ &= P_X\boldsymbol Y + P_{X\cap Z^\perp} \boldsymbol Y = \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_q + P_{X\cap Z^\perp} \boldsymbol Y \end{align*}\]

Èi din Teorema lui Pitagora (vezi triunghiul roÈu) deducem cÄ

\[ \lVert P_X\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2 = \lVert P_Z\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2 + \lVert P_{X\cap Z^\perp}\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2. \]

  1. DacÄ modelul nu are termenul liber (constanta) atunci coeficientul de determinare este definit prin \(R_X^2 = \frac{\lVert P_{X}\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2}{\lVert\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2}\) prin urmare

\[ R_X^2 = \frac{\lVert P_{X}\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2}{\lVert\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2} = \frac{\lVert P_Z\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2 + \lVert P_{X\cap Z^\perp}\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2}{\lVert\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2} = R_Z^2 + \frac{\lVert P_{X\cap Z^\perp}\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2}{\lVert\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2}\geq R_Z^2.\square \]

Rezultatul de mai sus se generalizeazÄ Èi Ã®n cazul modelelor imbricate care conÈin termenul constant Èi ne aratÄ cÄ modelul mai mare are un coeficient de determinare superior modelului mai mic. Altfel spus, dacÄ la un model dat adÄugÄm una sau mai multe variabile explicative ameliorÄm variabilitatea explicatÄ de model, chiar dacÄ variabilele explicative suplimentare nu sunt pertinente! Ãn acest caz este de preferat coeficientul de determinare ajustat.

6 Modelul (condiÈionat) normal

ConsiderÄm modelul de regresie \(\boldsymbol Y = \boldsymbol X\boldsymbol \beta + \boldsymbol \varepsilon\) Ã®n care \(\boldsymbol Y\in\mathbb{R}^n\) este vectorul rÄspuns, \(\boldsymbol X = \left[\mathbf{1}|\boldsymbol X_1|\cdots|\boldsymbol X_p\right]\in\mathcal{M}_{n, p+1}(\mathbb{R})\) este matricea de design, \(\boldsymbol \beta\in\mathbb{R}^{p+1}\) este vectorul parametrilor Èi \(\boldsymbol \varepsilon\in\mathbb{R}^n\) este vectorul termenilor eroare. PÃ¢nÄ acum, ipotezele modelului erau

\[ \begin{array}{ll} \mathcal{H}_1: \, rang(\boldsymbol X) = p+1\\ \mathcal{H}_2: \, \mathbb{E}[\boldsymbol \varepsilon] = 0,\, Var(\boldsymbol \varepsilon) = \sigma^2 I_n \end{array} \]

Èi proprietÄÈile estimatorilor rezultaÈi din metoda celor mai mici pÄtrate au fost obÈinute fÄrÄ a face apel la repartiÈia termenilor eroare.

Ãn aceastÄ secÈiune ne propunem sÄ studiem proprietÄÈile statistice ale modelului de regresie liniarÄ plasÃ¢ndu-ne Ã®ntr-un context parametric Èi anume Ã®n contextul modelului gaussian:

\[ \begin{array}{ll} \mathcal{H}_1: \, rang(\boldsymbol X) = p+1\\ \mathcal{H}_2': \, \boldsymbol \varepsilon \sim\mathcal{N}(0, \sigma^2 I_n) \end{array} \]

ObservÄm cÄ ipoteza \(\mathcal{H}_2'\) este un caz particular al ipotezei \(\mathcal{H}_2\) Èi Ã®n plus implicÄ faptul cÄ reziduurile sunt independente Èi identic repartizate condiÈie care nu era necesarÄ pÃ¢nÄ acum. Ipoteza de normalitate a erorilor ne permite sÄ scriem funcÈia de verosimilitate asociatÄ modelului, sÄ deducem repartiÈiile estimatorilor propuÈi, sÄ construim intervale de Ã®ncredere Èi sÄ testÄm ipoteze statistice asupra parametrilor modelului.

6.1 Estimatori de verosimilitate maximÄ

odatÄ cu ipoteza suplimentarÄ de normalitate a termenilor eroare, putem determina estimatorii de verosimilitate maximÄ. Rezultatul urmÄtor face legÄtura dintre estimatorii obÈinuÈi prin metoda celor mai mici pÄtrate din capitolul anterior Èi cei obÈinuÈi prin metoda verosimilitÄÈii maxime.

ConsiderÄm modelul de regresie liniarÄ \(\boldsymbol Y = \boldsymbol X\boldsymbol \beta + \boldsymbol\varepsilon\) sub ipotezele \(\mathcal{H}_1\) Èi \(\mathcal{H}_2'\) de mai sus. Atunci estimatorii de verosimilitate maximÄ pentru \(\boldsymbol \beta\) Èi \(\sigma^2\) sunt daÈi de

\[ \hat{\boldsymbol\beta}_{VM} = (\boldsymbol{X}^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol{X}^\intercal \boldsymbol Y, \quad \hat{\sigma}_{VM}^2 = \frac{\lVert\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol X\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}_{VM}\rVert^2}{n}=\frac{n - (p+1)}{n}\hat{\sigma}^2. \]

Ãncepem prin a observa cÄ din modelul de regresie

\[ y_i = \boldsymbol x_i^\intercal\boldsymbol\beta + \varepsilon_i \]

Èi conform ipotezei \(\mathcal{H}_2'\) avem \(\varepsilon_i\sim\mathcal{N}(0, \sigma^2)\) prin urmare \(y_i\sim\mathcal{N}(\boldsymbol x_i^\intercal\boldsymbol\beta, \sigma^2)\) Èi Ã®n plus \(y_i\) sunt variabile aleatoare independete deoarece \(\varepsilon_i\) sunt independente. Astfel funcÈia de verosimilitate se scrie

\[\begin{align*} L(\boldsymbol\beta, \sigma^2;\boldsymbol Y) &= \prod_{i = 1}^{n}f_{Y}(y_i) = \left(\frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi\sigma^2}}\right)^n e^{-\frac{1}{2\sigma^2}\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(y_i - \boldsymbol x_i^\intercal\boldsymbol\beta)^2} \\ &= \left(\frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi\sigma^2}}\right)^n e^{-\frac{1}{2\sigma^2}\lVert\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol X\boldsymbol\beta\rVert^2} \end{align*}\]

ceea ce conduce la logaritmul funcÈiei de verosimilitate

\[ \ell(\boldsymbol\beta, \sigma^2;\boldsymbol Y) = \log L(\boldsymbol\beta, \sigma^2;\boldsymbol Y) = -\frac{n}{2}\log{2\pi\sigma^2} -\frac{1}{2\sigma^2}\lVert\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol X\boldsymbol\beta\rVert^2. \]

Vrem sÄ determinÄm

\[ (\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}_{VM}, \hat{\sigma}_{VM}^2) = \underset{(\boldsymbol\beta, \sigma^2)\in\mathbb{R}^{p+1}\times(0,\infty)}{\arg\max} \ell(\boldsymbol\beta, \sigma^2;\boldsymbol Y) \]

Èi observÄm cÄ pentru \(\sigma^2\) fixat, a maximiza funcÈia \(\ell(\boldsymbol\beta, \sigma^2;\boldsymbol Y)\) revine la a determina valoarea lui \(\boldsymbol\beta\) care minimizeazÄ \(\lVert\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol X\boldsymbol\beta\rVert^2\), aceasta ne fiind alta decÃ¢t \(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}\) obÈinut prin metoda celor mai mici pÄtrate. Astfel gÄsim cÄ

\[ \hat{\boldsymbol\beta}_{VM} = \hat{\boldsymbol\beta} = (\boldsymbol{X}^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol{X}^\intercal \boldsymbol Y. \]

Pentru a determina \(\hat{\sigma}_{VM}^2\) sÄ observÄm cÄ problema revine la a determina soluÈia ecuaÈiei

\[ \frac{\partial l(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}_{VM}, \sigma^2;\boldsymbol Y)}{\partial \sigma^2} = -\frac{n}{2\sigma^2} + \frac{1}{2\sigma^4}\lVert\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol X\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}_{VM}\rVert^2 = 0 \]

care este \(\hat{\sigma}_{VM}^2 = \frac{\lVert\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol X\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}_{VM}\rVert^2}{n}=\frac{\lVert\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol X\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}\rVert^2}{n}\). ComparÃ¢nd acest rezultat cu cel obÈinut prin metoda celor mai mici pÄtrate observÄm cÄ

\[ \hat{\sigma}_{VM}^2 = \frac{n - (p+1)}{n}\hat{\sigma}^2, \]

deci estimatorul de verosimilitate maximÄ \(\hat{\sigma}_{VM}^2\) a lui \(\sigma^2\) est un estimator deplasat. \(\square\)

Se poate arÄta cÄ estimatorii de verosimilitate maximÄ \(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}_{VM} = \hat{\boldsymbol\beta}\) Èi \(\hat{\sigma}_{VM}^2 = \frac{n - (p+1)}{n}\hat{\sigma}^2\) Èi prin urmare Èi cei obÈinuÈi prin metoda celor mai mici pÄtrate sunt suficienÈi Ã®n sensul cÄ niciun alt estimator nu poate sÄ Ã®mbunÄtÄÈeascÄ estimarea lui \(\boldsymbol\beta\) Èi \(\sigma^2\) plecÃ¢nd de la eÈantionul dat (Rencher and Schaalje 2008). Mai mult, dacÄ Ã®n ipotezele \(\mathcal{H}_1\) Èi \(\mathcal{H}_2\) estimatorul \(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}\) era de varianÈÄ minimalÄ Ã®n clasa estimatorilor liniari nedeplasaÈi (Teorema Gauss-Markov - PropoziÈia ) Ã®n ipoteza suplimentarÄ de normalitate \(\mathcal{H}_2'\) acest rezultat se extinde la clasa tuturor estimatorilor nedeplasaÈi. Ãn acelaÈi mod Èi \(\hat{\sigma}^2\) are varianÈÄ minimalÄ Ã®n clasa tuturor estimatorilor nedeplasaÈi pentru \(\sigma^2\) (Rencher and Schaalje 2008).

Ãn cele ce urmeazÄ vom considera estimatorul nedeplasat \(\hat{\sigma}^2 = \frac{\lVert\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol X\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}\rVert^2}{n - (p+1)} = \frac{\sum_{i=1}^{n}\hat{\varepsilon}_i^2}{n - (p+1)}\) ca estimator al lui \(\sigma^2\).

6.2 RepartiÈiile estimatorilor

Ãnainte de a investiga repartiÈiile estimatorilor \(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}\) Èi \(\hat{\sigma}^2\) pentru modelul de regresie liniarÄ multiplÄ sub ipoteza de normalitate, sÄ reamintim cÃ¢teva noÈiuni legate de vectorii gaussieni (pentru mai multe detalii se poate consulta (Seber and Lee 2003, Capitolul 2) sau (Jacod and Protter 2003, Capitolul 16)).

Spunem cÄ un vector \(\boldsymbol Y = (Y_1,\ldots,Y_n)\in\mathbb{R}^n\) este un vector gaussian dacÄ toate combinaÈiile liniare \(\sum_{i=1}^{n}a_iY_i\) sunt repartizate normal (posibil degenerat dacÄ toÈi coeficienÈii sunt nuli). Acest vector admite o medie \(\boldsymbol\mu = \mathbb{E}[\boldsymbol Y]\) Èi o matrice de varianÈÄ-covarianÈÄ \(\Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y} = \mathbb{E}[(\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol\mu)(\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol\mu)^\intercal]\) care caracterizeazÄ complet repartiÈia lui \(\boldsymbol Y\). Ãn acest caz notÄm \(\boldsymbol Y \sim\mathcal{N}(\boldsymbol\mu, \Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y})\). Un vector gaussian \(\boldsymbol Y\) admite o densitate de repartiÈie \(f_{\boldsymbol Y}\) pe \(\mathbb{R}^n\) dacÄ Èi numai dacÄ matricea sa de varianÈÄ-covarianÈÄ \(\Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}\) este inversabilÄ Èi Ã®n acest caz

\[ f_{\boldsymbol Y}(\boldsymbol y) = \frac{1}{(2\pi)^{\frac{n}{2}}\sqrt{\det{\Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}}}} e^{-\frac{1}{2}(\boldsymbol y - \boldsymbol \mu)^\intercal \Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}^{-1}(\boldsymbol y - \boldsymbol \mu)} \]

Ãn cazul Ã®n care matricea \(\Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}\) nu este inversabilÄ Ã®nseamnÄ cÄ \(\boldsymbol Y\) ia valori Ã®ntr-un subspaÈiu de dimensiune \(n_0<n\) unde este repartizat ca un vector gaussian de dimensiune \(n_0\).

Figura de mai jos prezintÄ patru repartiÈii normale bivariate (\(n=2\)) \(\boldsymbol Y \sim\mathcal{N}(\boldsymbol\mu, \Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y})\), cu \(\boldsymbol\mu = (\mu_1, \mu_2)^\intercal\) iar \(\Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y} = \begin{pmatrix}\sigma_{11} & \sigma_{12}\\ \sigma_{21} & \sigma_{22}\end{pmatrix}= \begin{pmatrix}\sigma_{1}^2 & \sigma_{12}\\ \sigma_{12} & \sigma_{2}^2\end{pmatrix}\), rotite cu unghiul \(\alpha\). Ãn acest caz densitatea de repartiÈie este

\[ f_{\boldsymbol Y}(y_1,y_2) = \frac{1}{2\pi\sigma_1\sigma_2\sqrt{1-\rho^2}}e^{-\frac{1}{2(1-\rho^2)}\left[\left(\frac{y_1 - \mu_1}{\sigma_1}\right)^2 - 2\rho\left(\frac{y_1 - \mu_1}{\sigma_1}\right)\left(\frac{y_2 - \mu_2}{\sigma_2}\right) + \left(\frac{y_2 - \mu_2}{\sigma_2}\right)^2\right]} \]

unde \(\rho = \frac{\sigma_{12}}{\sigma_1\sigma_2}\) este coeficientul de corelaÈie.

Una dintre proprietÄÈile importante ale vectorilor gaussieni este stabilitatea prin transformÄri afine: dacÄ \(\boldsymbol A\in\mathcal{M}_{m,n}(\mathbb{R})\) Èi \(\boldsymbol b\in\mathcal{M}_{m,1}(\mathbb{R})\) sunt respectiv o matrice Èi un vector de scalari atunci

\[ \boldsymbol Y \sim\mathcal{N}(\boldsymbol\mu, \Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}) \Longrightarrow \boldsymbol A\boldsymbol Y + \boldsymbol b \sim\mathcal{N}(\boldsymbol A\boldsymbol\mu + \boldsymbol b, \boldsymbol A\Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}\boldsymbol A^\intercal) \]

De asemenea, plecÃ¢nd de la funcÈia caracteristicÄ, se poate verifica proprietatea de independenÈÄ a componentelor unui vector gaussian care ne spune cÄ acestea sunt independente dacÄ Èi numai dacÄ matricea de varianÈÄ-covarianÈÄ este o matrice diagonalÄ (Jacod and Protter 2003).

Avem urmÄtorul rezultat care face legÄtura dintre repartiÈia normalÄ Èi repartiÈia \(\chi^2\):

Fie \(\boldsymbol Y \sim\mathcal{N}(\boldsymbol\mu, \Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y})\) un vector gaussian Ã®n \(\mathbb{R}^n\). DacÄ \(\Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}\) este o matrice inversabilÄ atunci

\[ (\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol \mu)^\intercal \Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}^{-1}(\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol \mu) \sim \chi_n^2 \]

repartiÈia \(\chi^2\) cu \(n\) grade de libertate.

Deoarece matricea de varianÈÄ-covarianÈÄ \(\Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}\) este o matrice simetricÄ Èi pozitiv definitÄ atunci din Teorema de descompunere spectralÄ ea se poate descompune sub forma \(\Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y} = \boldsymbol Q\boldsymbol\Delta \boldsymbol Q^\intercal\) unde \(\boldsymbol Q = [\boldsymbol v_1,\ldots,\boldsymbol v_n]\) este o matrice ortogonalÄ (\(\boldsymbol Q^\intercal = \boldsymbol Q^{-1}\)) formatÄ din vectorii proprii \(\boldsymbol v_1,\ldots,\boldsymbol v_n\) corespunzÄtori valorilor proprii \(\lambda_1,\ldots,\lambda_n\), iar \(\boldsymbol \Delta\) este matricea diagonalÄ \(\mathrm{diag}(\lambda_1,\ldots,\lambda_n)\). DacÄ notÄm cu \(\boldsymbol \Delta^{-\frac{1}{2}}\) matricea diagonalÄ de coeficienÈi diagonali \(\frac{1}{\sqrt{\lambda_1}},\ldots,\frac{1}{\sqrt{\lambda_n}}\) (aceste fracÈii existÄ deoarece pozitiv definirea matricei \(\Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}\) implicÄ faptul cÄ valorile proprii \(\lambda_i>0\), \(i = 1,\ldots,n\)) atunci

\[ \Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y} = \boldsymbol Q\boldsymbol\Delta \boldsymbol Q^\intercal \Longrightarrow \Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}^{-1} = \boldsymbol Q\boldsymbol\Delta^{-1} \boldsymbol Q^\intercal = \left(\boldsymbol Q\boldsymbol\Delta^{-\frac{1}{2}} \boldsymbol Q^\intercal\right)\left(\boldsymbol Q\boldsymbol\Delta^{-\frac{1}{2}} \boldsymbol Q^\intercal\right) = \Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}^{-\frac{1}{2}}\Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}^{-\frac{1}{2}}. \]

Prin urmare gÄsim cÄ

\[ (\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol \mu)^\intercal \Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}^{-1}(\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol \mu) = \left(\Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}^{-\frac{1}{2}}(\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol \mu)\right)^\intercal\left(\Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}^{-\frac{1}{2}}(\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol \mu)\right) \]

Èi cum vectorii gaussieni rÄmÃ¢n gaussieni Èi prin aplicarea unor transformÄri afine (vezi rezultatul de mai sus) avem cÄ

\[ \boldsymbol Y \sim\mathcal{N}(\boldsymbol\mu, \Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}) \Longrightarrow \Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}^{-\frac{1}{2}}(\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol \mu) \sim\mathcal{N}(0, I_n). \]

Astfel vectorul \(\boldsymbol V = [\boldsymbol V_1,\ldots,\boldsymbol V_n]^\intercal = \Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}^{-\frac{1}{2}}(\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol \mu)\), care nu este altceva decÃ¢t vectorul \(\boldsymbol Y\) centrat Èi redus, este gaussian standard (\(\boldsymbol V_j\sim\mathcal{N}(0,1)\) Èi \(\boldsymbol V_i\) Èi \(\boldsymbol V_j\) sunt independente) Èi

\[ (\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol \mu)^\intercal \Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}^{-1}(\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol \mu) = \lVert \boldsymbol V\rVert^2 = \boldsymbol V_1^2 + \cdots + \boldsymbol V_n^2\sim\chi^2_n. \square \]

UrmÄtorul rezultat, cunoscut sub denumirea de Teorema lui Cochran (a se vedea (Sen and Srivastava 2012) sau (Greene 2011) pentru o demonstraÈie a acestui rezultat), asigurÄ cÄ descompunerea unui vector gaussian Ã®n componente independente pe subspaÈii ortogonale ne dÄ vectori independenÈi a cÄror repartiÈie o putem explicita. AceastÄ teoremÄ poate fi vÄzutÄ Èi ca o generalizare a Teoremei lui Pitagora:

Fie \(\boldsymbol Y \sim\mathcal{N}(\boldsymbol\mu, \sigma^2 I_n)\), \(\mathcal{M}\subset\mathbb{R}^n\) un subspaÈiu de dimensiune \(p\), \(P\) matricea de proiecÈie ortogonalÄ pe \(\mathcal{M}\) Èi \(P_\perp = I_n - P\) matricea de proiecÈie ortogonalÄ pe \(\mathcal{M}^\perp\). Au loc urmÄtoarele proprietÄÈi:

  1. \(P\boldsymbol Y\sim\mathcal{N}(P\boldsymbol\mu, \sigma^2 P)\) Èi \(P_\perp\boldsymbol Y\sim\mathcal{N}(P_\perp\boldsymbol\mu, \sigma^2 P_\perp)\)

  2. vectorii \(P\boldsymbol Y\) Èi \(P_\perp\boldsymbol Y = \boldsymbol Y - P\boldsymbol Y\) sunt independenÈi

  3. \(\frac{\lVert P(\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol\mu)\rVert^2}{\sigma^2}\sim\chi_p^2\) Èi \(\frac{\lVert P_\perp(\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol\mu)\rVert^2}{\sigma^2}\sim\chi_{n-p}^2\).

Acum avem instrumentele necesare pentru a deduce repartiÈiile estimatorilor Ã®n modelul gaussian de regresie liniarÄ.

ConsiderÄm modelul de regresie liniarÄ \(\boldsymbol Y = \boldsymbol X\boldsymbol \beta + \boldsymbol \varepsilon\), sub ipotezele \(\mathcal{H}_1\) Èi \(\mathcal{H}_2'\). DacÄ presupunem cÄ varianÈa \(\sigma^2\) este cunoscutÄ atunci au loc proprietÄÈile

  1. Vectorul \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) este un vector gaussian de medie \(\boldsymbol \beta\) Èi matrice de varianÈÄ-covarianÈÄ \(\sigma^2(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\), i.e.Â \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\sim\mathcal{N}(\boldsymbol \beta, \sigma^2(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1})\)

  2. \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) Èi \(\hat{\sigma}^2\) sunt independenÈi

  3. \([n-(p+1)]\frac{\hat{\sigma}^2}{\sigma^2}\sim\chi^2_{n-(p+1)}\)

  1. Pentru a arÄta cÄ vectorul \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) este un vector gaussian vom folosi expresia acestuia obÈinutÄ prin metoda celor mai mici pÄtrate

\[ \hat{\boldsymbol \beta} = (\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol Y = (\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol X^\intercal(\boldsymbol X\boldsymbol \beta + \boldsymbol \varepsilon) = \boldsymbol \beta + (\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol \varepsilon. \]

Conform ipotezei \(\mathcal{H}_2'\), \(\boldsymbol \varepsilon\sim\mathcal{N}(0,\sigma^2 I_n)\) este un vector gaussian prin urmare Èi \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta} = \boldsymbol \beta + \underbrace{(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol X^\intercal}_{\boldsymbol A} \boldsymbol \varepsilon\) este tot un vector gaussian repartizat

\[ \hat{\boldsymbol \beta} = \boldsymbol \beta + \underbrace{(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol X^\intercal}_{\boldsymbol A} \boldsymbol \varepsilon = \boldsymbol \beta + \boldsymbol A\boldsymbol \varepsilon \sim \mathcal{N}\left(\boldsymbol \beta, \boldsymbol A \sigma^2 I_n\boldsymbol A^\intercal\right) = \mathcal{N}\left(\boldsymbol \beta, \sigma^2(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\right) \] deoarece \(\boldsymbol A \sigma^2 I_n\boldsymbol A^\intercal = (\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol X^\intercal \sigma^2 I_n \boldsymbol X(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1} = \sigma^2(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\).

  1. Fie \(\mathcal{M}(X)\) subspaÈiul lui \(\mathbb{R}^n\) generat de coloanele matricei \(\boldsymbol X\) Èi fie \(P_{X} = \boldsymbol X(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol X^\intercal\) matricea de proiecÈie ortogonalÄ pe \(\mathcal{M}(X)\). Avem

\[ \hat{\boldsymbol \beta} = (\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol Y = (\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol X^\intercal\left(\underbrace{\boldsymbol X(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol X^\intercal}_{=P_X}\right)\boldsymbol Y = (\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol X^\intercal P_X\boldsymbol Y \]

prin urmare \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) este un vector aleator ce depinde de \(P_X\boldsymbol Y\). ObservÄm de asemenea cÄ din definiÈia lui \(\hat{\sigma}^2\),

\[ \hat{\sigma}^2 = \frac{\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol\varepsilon}\rVert^2}{n - (p+1)} = \frac{\lVert \boldsymbol Y - P_X\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2}{n - (p+1)} \] acesta este o funcÈie de \(\boldsymbol Y - P_X\boldsymbol Y\). AplicÃ¢nd Teorema lui Cochran (PropoziÈia de mai sus) observÄm cÄ vectorii \(P_X\boldsymbol Y\) Èi \(\boldsymbol Y - P_X\boldsymbol Y\) sunt independenÈi prin urmare Èi \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) Èi \(\hat{\sigma}^2\) sunt independenÈi ca funcÈii de vectori independenÈi.

  1. NotÃ¢nd cu \(P_{X^\perp}\) proiecÈia ortogonalÄ pe subspaÈiul ortogonal \(\mathcal{M}(X)^\perp\), subspaÈiu de dimensiune \(n-(p+1)\), avem

\[ \hat{\boldsymbol\varepsilon} = \boldsymbol Y - P_X\boldsymbol Y = P_{X^\perp}\boldsymbol Y = P_{X^\perp}(\underbrace{\boldsymbol X\boldsymbol \beta}_{\in\mathcal{M}(X)} + \boldsymbol \varepsilon) = P_{X^\perp}\boldsymbol \varepsilon, \]

unde \(\boldsymbol \varepsilon\sim\mathcal{N}(0,\sigma^2 I_n)\).

Din Teorema lui Cochran gÄsim cÄ

\[ (n-(p+1))\frac{\hat{\sigma}^2}{\sigma^2} = \frac{\lVert P_{X^\perp}\boldsymbol \varepsilon\rVert^2}{\sigma^2} = \frac{\lVert P_{X^\perp}\left(\boldsymbol \varepsilon - \mathbb{E}[\boldsymbol \varepsilon]\right)\rVert^2}{\sigma^2}\sim \chi^2_{n - (p+1)}. \square \] Putem observa cÄ rezultatul anterior nu este suficient pentru a determina o regiune de Ã®ncredere pentru coeficienÈii modelului de regresie \(\boldsymbol \beta\) deoarece varianÈa \(\sigma^2\) a fost presupusÄ cunoscutÄ, fenomen care nu este aplicabil Ã®n caz general. Rezultatul urmÄtor vine sÄ acopere acest deficit.

ConsiderÄm modelul de regresie liniarÄ \(\boldsymbol Y = \boldsymbol X\boldsymbol \beta + \boldsymbol \varepsilon\), sub ipotezele \(\mathcal{H}_1\) Èi \(\mathcal{H}_2'\) Èi presupunem cÄ varianÈa \(\sigma^2\) nu este cunoscutÄ. Atunci au loc proprietÄÈile

  1. pentru \(j\in\{0,1,\ldots, p\}\), notÃ¢nd cu \(\left[(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\right]_{j+1,j+1}\) elementul \(j+1\) de pe diagonala matricei \((\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\), avem

\[ \hat{\beta}_j\sim \mathcal{N}(\beta_j, \sigma^2\left[(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\right]_{j+1,j+1}), \quad T_j = \frac{\hat{\beta}_j - \beta_j}{\hat{\sigma}\sqrt{\left[(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\right]_{j+1,j+1}}} = \frac{\hat{\beta}_j - \beta_j}{\hat{\sigma}_{\hat{\beta}_j}}\sim t_{n-(p+1)} \]

  1. fie \(R\in\mathcal{M}_{q,p+1}(\mathbb{R})\) o matrice de rang \(q\) (\(q\leq p+1\)) atunci

\[ \frac{1}{q\hat{\sigma}^2}\left(R(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta} - \boldsymbol\beta)\right)^\intercal\left[R(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}R^\intercal\right]^{-1}R(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta} - \boldsymbol\beta) \sim F_{q, n - (p+1)} \]

  1. Din PropoziÈia am vÄzut cÄ \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\sim\mathcal{N}(\boldsymbol \beta, \sigma^2(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1})\) prin urmare

\[ \hat{\beta}_j\sim \mathcal{N}(\beta_j, \sigma^2\left[(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\right]_{j+1,j+1}) \]

ceea ce implicÄ \(\frac{\hat{\beta}_j - \beta_j}{\sigma\sqrt{\left[(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\right]_{j+1,j+1}}}\sim\mathcal{N}(0,1)\).

Scriind

\[ T_j = \frac{\frac{\hat{\beta}_j - \beta_j}{\sigma\sqrt{\left[(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\right]_{j+1,j+1}}}}{\frac{\hat{\sigma}}{\sigma}} = \frac{\frac{\hat{\beta}_j - \beta_j}{\sigma\sqrt{\left[(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\right]_{j+1,j+1}}}}{\sqrt{\frac{(n - (p+1))\frac{\hat{\sigma}^2}{\sigma^2}}{n-(p+1)}}} \]

Èi ÈinÃ¢nd cont de faptul cÄ \((n-(p+1))\frac{\hat{\sigma}^2}{\sigma^2}\sim\chi^2_{n-(p+1)}\) iar \(\hat{\beta}_j\) Èi \(\hat{\sigma}^2\) sunt independente, deducem cÄ \(T_j \sim t_{n-(p+1)}\).

  1. SÄ remarcÄm cÄ matricea \(R(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}R^\intercal\) pÄtraticÄ de ordin \(q\) este inversabilÄ deoarece matricea \((\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\) este de rang \(p+1\), \(p+1\geq q\). Cum \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) este un vector gaussian deducem cÄ Èi \(R\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) este un vector gaussian de medie Èi matrice de covarianÈÄ

\[ R\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\sim\mathcal{N}\left(R\boldsymbol \beta, \sigma^2 R(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1} R^\intercal\right) \]

Astfel, conform PropoziÈiei privind legÄtura dintre repartiÈia normalÄ Èi repartiÈia \(\chi^2\), rezultÄ cÄ

\[ \frac{1}{\sigma^2}\left(R(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta} - \boldsymbol\beta)\right)^\intercal\left[R(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}R^\intercal\right]^{-1}R(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta} - \boldsymbol\beta)\sim \chi^2_q. \]

Ãn expresia de mai sus, Ã®nlocuim pe \(\sigma^2\) cu \(\hat{\sigma}^2\) Èi ÈinÃ¢nd cont cÄ \(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}\) Èi \(\hat{\sigma}^2\) sunt independente iar \((n-(p+1))\frac{\hat{\sigma}^2}{\sigma^2}\sim\chi^2_{n-(p+1)}\) concluzionÄm cÄ

\[ \frac{1}{q\hat{\sigma}^2}\left(R(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta} - \boldsymbol\beta)\right)^\intercal\left[R(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}R^\intercal\right]^{-1}R(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta} - \boldsymbol\beta) = \frac{\frac{\frac{1}{\sigma^2}\left(R(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta} - \boldsymbol\beta)\right)^\intercal\left[R(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}R^\intercal\right]^{-1}R(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta} - \boldsymbol\beta)}{q}}{\frac{(n-(p+1))\frac{\hat{\sigma}^2}{\sigma^2}}{n-(p+1)}} \sim\frac{\frac{\chi^2_q}{q}}{\frac{\chi^2_{n - (p+1)}}{n-(p+1)}} = F_{q, n - (p+1)}.\square \]

Exemplu: aplicaÈie pentru regresia liniarÄ simplÄ

Vom exemplifica rezultatul celui de-al doilea subpunct al PropoziÈiei pentru cazul particular Ã®n care \(p+1=q=2\) iar matricea \(R=I_2\). Avem cÄ

\[ R(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta} - \boldsymbol\beta) = \begin{pmatrix}\hat{\beta}_0 - \beta_0\\ \hat{\beta}_1 - \beta_1\end{pmatrix} \]

Èi dacÄ termenul liber face parte din modelul de regresie atunci matricea \(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X\) devine (a se vedea Èi Exemplul )

\[ \boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X = \begin{pmatrix}n & \sum x_i\\ \sum x_i & \sum x_i^2\end{pmatrix}. \]

Astfel gÄsim cÄ \(\frac{1}{q\hat{\sigma}^2}\left(R(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta} - \boldsymbol\beta)\right)^\intercal\left[R(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}R^\intercal\right]^{-1}R(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta} - \boldsymbol\beta)\) se rescrie ca

\[ \frac{1}{2\hat{\sigma}^2}\left[n(\hat{\beta}_0 - \beta_0)^2 + 2n\bar{x}(\hat{\beta}_0 - \beta_0)(\hat{\beta}_1 - \beta_1) + \sum_{i=1}^{n}x_i^2(\hat{\beta}_1 - \beta_1)^2\right] \sim F_{2, n - 2} \]

proprietate care coincide cu rezultatul obÈinut Ã®n cazul regresiei liniare simple. Mai mult, dacÄ \(p+1 = q\) Èi \(R = I_{p+1}\) atunci repartiÈia distanÈei (ponderate de inversa matricei de covarianÈÄ) dintre estimatorul obÈinut prin metoda celor mai mici pÄtrate \(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}\) Èi valoarea realÄ \(\boldsymbol \beta\) este \(F_{p+1, n - (p+1)}\):

\[ \frac{1}{\hat{\sigma}^2(p+1)}(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta} - \boldsymbol\beta)^\intercal(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta} - \boldsymbol\beta)\sim F_{p+1, n - (p+1)}. \]

6.3 Intervale Èi regiuni de Ã®ncredere

Rezultatele din propoziÈiile anterioare conduc la urmÄtoarele intervale (atunci cÃ¢nd parametrii sunt consideraÈi separat) Èi regiuni de Ã®ncredere (atunci cÃ¢nd luÄm Ã®n calcul mai mulÈi parametrii simultan prin urmare Èinem cont Èi de dependenÈa dintre ei) pentru parametrii modelului de regresie liniarÄ:

  1. Un interval de Ã®ncredere bilateral de nivel de Ã®ncredere \(1-\alpha\) pentru parametrul \(\beta_j\), \(j\in\{0,1,\ldots,p\}\) este dat de

\[ IC^{1-\alpha}(\beta_j) = \left[\hat{\beta}_j - t_{n-(p+1)}\left(1-\frac{\alpha}{2}\right)\hat{\sigma}\sqrt{\left[(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\right]_{j+1,j+1}}, \hat{\beta}_j + t_{n-(p+1)}\left(1-\frac{\alpha}{2}\right)\hat{\sigma}\sqrt{\left[(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\right]_{j+1,j+1}}\right] \] unde \(t_{n-(p+1)}\left(1-\frac{\alpha}{2}\right)\) este cuantila de ordin \(1-\frac{\alpha}{2}\) a repartiÈiei Student \(t_{n-(p+1)}\).

  1. Un interval de Ã®ncredere bilateral de nivel de Ã®ncredere \(1-\alpha\) pentru \(\sigma^2\) este dat de

\[ IC^{1-\alpha}(\sigma^2) = \left[\frac{[n - (p+1)]\hat{\sigma}^2}{\chi^2_{n - (p+1)}\left(1-\frac{\alpha}{2}\right)}, \frac{[n - (p+1)]\hat{\sigma}^2}{\chi^2_{n - (p+1)}\left(\frac{\alpha}{2}\right)}\right] \]

unde \(\chi^2_{n - (p+1)}\left(1-\frac{\alpha}{2}\right)\) Èi \(\chi^2_{n - (p+1)}\left(\frac{\alpha}{2}\right)\) sunt cuantilele de ordin \(1-\frac{\alpha}{2}\) Èi respectiv \(\frac{\alpha}{2}\) a repartiÈiei \(\chi^2_{n - (p+1)}\).

  1. O regiune de Ã®ncredere de nivel de Ã®ncredere \(1-\alpha\) pentru \(q\) (\(q\leq p+1\)) parametrii \(\beta_j\), notaÈi \((\beta_{j_1},\ldots,\beta_{j_q})\), este datÄ de
  • atunci cÃ¢nd \(\sigma\) este cunoscutÄ, de

\[ RC^{1-\alpha}(R\boldsymbol \beta) = \left\{R\boldsymbol \beta\in\mathbb{R}^q\,|\, \frac{1}{\sigma^2}\left(R(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta} - \boldsymbol\beta)\right)^\intercal\left[R(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}R^\intercal\right]^{-1}R(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta} - \boldsymbol\beta) \leq \chi^2_q(1-\alpha)\right\} \]

  • atunci cÃ¢nd \(\sigma\) este necunoscutÄ, de

\[ RC^{1-\alpha}(R\boldsymbol \beta) = \left\{R\boldsymbol \beta\in\mathbb{R}^q\,|\, \frac{1}{q\hat{\sigma}^2}\left(R(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta} - \boldsymbol\beta)\right)^\intercal\left[R(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}R^\intercal\right]^{-1}R(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta} - \boldsymbol\beta) \leq f_{q, n - (p+1)}(1-\alpha)\right\} \]

unde \(R\) este o matrice de dimensiune \(q\times(p+1)\) cu toate elementele nule exceptÃ¢nd elementele \(R_{i,j_i}\) care sunt egale cu \(1\) iar \(f_{q, n - (p+1)}(1-\alpha)\) este cuantila de ordin \(1-\alpha\) a repartiÈiei Fisher-Snedecor \(F_{q, n - (p+1)}\) cu \(q\) grade de libertate la numÄrÄtor Èi \(n-(p+1)\) grade de libertate la numitor.

Exemplu: regiune de Ã®ncredere caz particular

Ca ilustrare a regiunii de Ã®ncredere de mai sus, sÄ presupunem cÄ \(p\geq 2\) Èi \(q = 2\) iar matricea \(R\) este

\[ R = \begin{pmatrix}1 & 0 & 0 & \cdots & 0\\ 0 & 1 & 0 & \cdots & 0\end{pmatrix} \]

ceea ce conduce la \(R(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta} - \boldsymbol\beta) = \begin{pmatrix}\hat{\beta}_0 - \beta_0\\ \hat{\beta}_1 - \beta_1\end{pmatrix}\). DacÄ presupunem cÄ \(\sigma^2\) este necunoscut atunci regiunea de Ã®ncredere pentru \((\beta_0,\beta_1)\) este datÄ de

\[ \small RC^{1-\alpha}(\beta_0,\beta_1) = \left\{(\beta_0,\beta_1)\in\mathbb{R}^2\,|\, \frac{1}{2\hat{\sigma}^2}\begin{pmatrix}\hat{\beta}_0 - \beta_0 & \hat{\beta}_1 - \beta_1\end{pmatrix}\left[R(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}R^\intercal\right]^{-1}\begin{pmatrix}\hat{\beta}_0 - \beta_0\\ \hat{\beta}_1 - \beta_1\end{pmatrix} \leq f_{2, n - (p+1)}(1-\alpha)\right\} \normalsize \]

Èi notÃ¢nd cu \(c_{ij}\) elementul de pe linia \(i\) coloana \(j\) a matricei \((\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\), gÄsim cÄ

\[ RC^{1-\alpha}(\beta_0,\beta_1) = \left\{(\beta_0,\beta_1)\in\mathbb{R}^2\,|\,\frac{c_{22}(\hat{\beta}_0 - \beta_0)^2 - 2c_{12}(\hat{\beta}_0 - \beta_0)(\hat{\beta}_1 - \beta_1) + c_{11}(\hat{\beta}_1 - \beta_1)^2}{2\hat{\sigma}^2(c_{11}c_{22} - c_{12}^2)}\leq f_{2, n - (p+1)}(1-\alpha)\right\} \]

ceea ce aratÄ cÄ regiunea are formÄ de elipsÄ (vezi (Ornea and Turtoi 2000, Capitolul 2, SecÈiunea 16)). Figura urmÄtoare ilustreazÄ aceastÄ regiune pentru date simulate conform modelului de regresie liniarÄ simplÄ \(y_i = 3 + 7x_i - \varepsilon_i\), cu \(x_i\sim\mathcal{U}[-5, 5]\) iar \(\varepsilon_i\sim\mathcal{N}(0, 4)\):

Exemplu: preÈul chiriilor Ã®n Munchen

Ãn acest exemplu vom explicita relaÈia dintre preÈul chiriei pe metrul pÄtrat Ã®n raport cu inversul suprafeÈei de locuit Èi anul de construcÈie a imobilului folosid modelul de regresie prezentat Ã®n Exemplul Ã®n care am considerat variabila centratÄ \(suprafata{\_}inv{\_}cen\) Èi variabilele ortogonale \(an{\_}co{\_}j\)

\[ \widehat{pret{\_m^2}_i} = \beta_0 + \beta_1 \times suprafata{\_inv\_cen} + \beta_2\times an{\_co\_1} + \beta_3\times an{\_co\_2} +\beta_4\times an{\_co\_3} \] Modelul estimat este

Intervalele de Ã®ncredere pentru coeficienÈii modelului de regresie la un nivel de Ã®ncredere de \(1-\alpha = 95\%\) sunt

\[ IC(\hat{\sigma}^2)^{1-\alpha} = \left[3.9591228, 4.3753046\right]. \] Ãn figura de mai jos sunt prezentate regiunile de Ã®ncredere pentru toate perechile de parametrii ai modelului Ã®mpreunÄ cu intervalele de Ã®ncredere corespunzÄtoare (elipse versus dreptunghiuri):

Atunci cÃ¢nd vrem sÄ facem o predicÈie dorim sÄ evaluÄm certitudinea cu care aceastÄ predicÈie este efectuatÄ. AvÃ¢nd Ã®n vedere variabilitate noi valori pe care vrem sÄ o prezicem este de aÈteptat ca intervalul de predicÈie sÄ fie mai mare decÃ¢t cel de Ã®ncredere la acelaÈi nivel de Ã®ncredere.

Fie \((x_{n+1,1}, \ldots, x_{n+1,p})\) o nouÄ observaÈie Èi considerÄm \(\boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal = (1, x_{n+1,1}, \ldots, x_{n+1,p})\). Ne propunem sÄ prezicem valoarea \(y_{n+1}\) conform modelului

\[ y_{n+1} = \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal\boldsymbol \beta + \varepsilon_{n+1} \]

cu \(\varepsilon_{n+1}\sim\mathcal{N}(0,\sigma^2)\) independentÄ de \(\varepsilon_i\), \(1\leq i\leq n\).

ArÄtaÈi cÄ un interval de predicÈie de nivel de Ã®ncredere \(1-\alpha\) pentru \(y_{n+1}\) este dat de

\[ \scriptsize \left[\boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal \hat{\boldsymbol \beta} - t_{n-(p+1)}\left(1-\frac{\alpha}{2}\right)\hat{\sigma}\sqrt{1 + \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol x_{n+1}}, \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal \hat{\boldsymbol \beta} + t_{n-(p+1)}\left(1-\frac{\alpha}{2}\right)\hat{\sigma}\sqrt{1 + \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol x_{n+1}}\right] \normalsize \]

PlecÃ¢nd de la un eÈantion de talie \(n\), \((\boldsymbol x_1, y_1), \ldots, (\boldsymbol x_n, y_n)\), gÄsim estimatorul de verosimilitate maximÄ (acelaÈi cu cel obÈinut prin metoda celor mai mici pÄtrate) \(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}\) a lui \(\boldsymbol\beta\) cu ajutorul cÄruia putem prezice valoarea \(\hat{y}_{n+1}\) dupÄ relaÈia

\[ \hat{y}_{n+1} = \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}. \]

Pentru a cuantifica eroarea de predicÈie \(y_{n+1} - \hat{y}_{n+1}\) folosim urmÄtoarea descompunere

\[ y_{n+1} - \hat{y}_{n+1} = \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal\left(\boldsymbol \beta - \hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\right) + \varepsilon_{n+1}, \]

care este o sumÄ de douÄ variabile gaussiene independente, \(\varepsilon_{n+1}\) Èi \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) care este un vector gaussian care depinde de \(\varepsilon_i\), \(1\leq i\leq n\).
